This example was contributed by Reinhard Schiedermeier
(schieder <at> informatik.fh).
It allows two RCXs to communicate with each other. 

% make

links the two programs together into one binary and
downloads it to one RCX. Load it onto both RCX, then
use the Prgm button to select program 0 on the first
and program 1 on the second RCX, then start them.
